nodes.text: I think airlines know well in advance which flights are subject to being over sold and have repeated bumping.
Feedback Commenter (164): I think airlines know well in advance which flights are subject to being over sold and have repeated bumping.
Annot: I think airlines know well in advance which flights are subject to being over sold and have repeated bumping.
For repeated bumping on the same flight same day of the week three or more weeks in a row, the specified compensation should double.
Feedback Commenter (164): For repeated bumping on the same flight same day of the week three or more weeks in a row, the specified compensation should double.
Annot: For repeated bumping on the same flight same day of the week three or more weeks in a row, the specified compensation should double.

Airlines should also notify passengeres when a flight is being significantly oversold and offer the denied boarding compensation in advance of the departure date for say 50% of the denied boarding compensation rate payable at the gate to reduce bumping from overbooking.

Feedback Commenter (164): Airlines should also notify passengeres when a flight is being significantly oversold and offer the denied boarding compensation in advance of the departure date for say 50% of the denied boarding compensation rate payable at the gate to reduce bumping from overbooking.

Annot: Airlines should also notify passengeres when a flight is being significantly oversold and offer the denied boarding compensation in advance of the departure date for say 50% of the denied boarding compensation rate payable at the gate to reduce bumping from overbooking.
I would prefer to be notified in advance and offered alternatives if I were being bumped rather than being blindsided at the airport. when it may be too late to explore other options.

AK traveler(287): I would prefer to be notified in advance and offered alternatives if I were being bumped rather than being blindsided at the airport. when it may be too late to explore other options.
Annot: I would prefer to be notified in advance and offered alternatives if I were being bumped rather than being blindsided at the airport. when it may be too late to explore other options.
Perhaps the airlines could ask  at the time of making the reservation, if the passenger would be willing to be bumped should the flight be overbooked.
AK traveler(287): Perhaps the airlines could ask  at the time of making the reservation, if the passenger would be willing to be bumped should the flight be overbooked.
Annot: Perhaps the airlines could ask  at the time of making the reservation, if the passenger would be willing to be bumped should the flight be overbooked.
The overbooking policy could be posted on line or explained if making the reservation in person.
AK traveler(287): The overbooking policy could be posted on line or explained if making the reservation in person.
Annot: The overbooking policy could be posted on line or explained if making the reservation in person.
The airline could call in adnvance and give the passenger their options (chance it that someone will be a no show, change the reservation) in addition to any required compensation.
AK traveler(287): The airline could call in adnvance and give the passenger their options (chance it that someone will be a no show, change the reservation) in addition to any required compensation.
Annot: The airline could call in adnvance and give the passenger their options (chance it that someone will be a no show, change the reservation) in addition to any required compensation.
I feel compensation should be made in kind to the 'currency' used to purchase the ticket.
AK traveler(287): I feel compensation should be made in kind to the 'currency' used to purchase the ticket.
Annot: I feel compensation should be made in kind to the 'currency' used to purchase the ticket.
I do not think it is fair for an airline to give miles in lieu of monetary compensation.
AK traveler(287): I do not think it is fair for an airline to give miles in lieu of monetary compensation.
Annot: I do not think it is fair for an airline to give miles in lieu of monetary compensation.
Advanced notification would help to possibly get another flight.
jbaker(301): Advanced notification would help to possibly get another flight.
Annot: Advanced notification would help to possibly get another flight.
In a perfect world they would sell the number of seats they have.
jbaker(301): In a perfect world they would sell the number of seats they have.
Annot: In a perfect world they would sell the number of seats they have.
The problem can't be solved this way.
SofieM(947): The problem can't be solved this way.
Annot: The problem can't be solved this way.
Airlines know ahead of time that flights are oversold, but they don't know whether all ticketed customers will show up on time or at all.
SofieM(947): Airlines know ahead of time that flights are oversold, but they don't know whether all ticketed customers will show up on time or at all.
Annot: Airlines know ahead of time that flights are oversold, but they don't know whether all ticketed customers will show up on time or at all.
For example, recently I got a free roundtrip flight with frequent flier miles, even though I only needed a oneway trip (only a roundtrip was available for the frequent flier miles).
SofieM(947): For example, recently I got a free roundtrip flight with frequent flier miles, even though I only needed a oneway trip (only a roundtrip was available for the frequent flier miles).
Annot: For example, recently I got a free roundtrip flight with frequent flier miles, even though I only needed a oneway trip (only a roundtrip was available for the frequent flier miles).
Of course, I never showed up for the return flight, because I never intended to return.
SofieM(947): Of course, I never showed up for the return flight, because I never intended to return.
Annot: Of course, I never showed up for the return flight, because I never intended to return.
If this flight had been oversold, the airline would know ahead of time, but they would not have known that I only got a roundtrip flight because it was my only option.
SofieM(947): If this flight had been oversold, the airline would know ahead of time, but they would not have known that I only got a roundtrip flight because it was my only option.
Annot: If this flight had been oversold, the airline would know ahead of time, but they would not have known that I only got a roundtrip flight because it was my only option.

Airlines could send out a notice to customers that the flight had been oversold, but they can't know until the customers have checked in/begun boarding whether all the ticketed customers are present or not.

SofieM(947): Airlines could send out a notice to customers that the flight had been oversold, but they can't know until the customers have checked in/begun boarding whether all the ticketed customers are present or not.

Annot: Airlines could send out a notice to customers that the flight had been oversold, but they can't know until the customers have checked in/begun boarding whether all the ticketed customers are present or not.
Unfortunately, there's no way to give advance notice.

Annot: Unfortunately, there's no way to give advance notice.
